The International '''Summer School Marktoberdorf''' is an annual two-week [[summer school]] for international [[computer science]] and [[mathematics]] postgraduate students and other young researchers, held annually since 1970 in [[Marktoberdorf]], near [[Munich]] in southern [[Germany]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.all-in.de/nachrichten/lokales/Informatiker-aus-aller-Welt-bei-Summer-School-in-Marktoberdorf;art26090,2042092 | title=Informatiker aus aller Welt bei Summer School in Marktoberdorf | website=all-in.de | location=Germany | language=German | date=9 August 2015 | accessdate=1 September 2015 }}</ref> Students are accommodated in the [[boarding house]] of a local high school, [[Gymnasium Marktoberdorf]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.gymnasium-marktoberdorf.de/ | title=Gymnasium Marktoberdorf | location=Germany | accessdate=1 September 2015 }}</ref> [[Proceedings]] are published when appropriate.<ref name="broy82" />
==Status== This is a summer school for [[theoretical computer science]] researchers,<ref>{{cite web| url=http://listserv.acm.org/scripts/wa-acmlpx.exe?A2=ind1101&L=seworld&F=&S=&P=25442 | title=[Summer School Marktoberdorf 2011] *Call for Application* | first=Katharina | last=Spies | date=28 January 2011 | work=SEWORLD Archives | publisher=[[Association for Computing Machinery|ACM]] | accessdate=2 September 2015 }}</ref> with some directors/co-directors who are [[ACM Turing Award]] winners (the nearest equivalent to the [[Nobel Prize]] in computer science).<ref name="turing-award">{{cite web| url=http://amturing.acm.org/byyear.cfm | title=Chronological Listing of A.M. Turing Award Winners | website=amturing.acm.org/ | publisher=ACM | accessdate=2 September 2015 }}</ref>
The summer school is supported as an Advanced Study Institute of the [[NATO Science for Peace and Security]] Program.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.nato.int/cps/en/natolive/news_65981.htm | title=NATO science programme aims to secure computer systems and networks | publisher=[[North Atlantic Treaty Organization]] | date=3 September 2010 | accessdate=2 September 2015 }}</ref> It is administered by the Faculty of Informatics at the [[Technical University of Munich]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.daad.de/deutschland/studienangebote/international-programs/en/?p=d&s=sk&id=90 | title=International Programmes in Germany 2015 – International Summer School Marktoberdorf 2015: Verification and Synthesis of Correct and Secure Systems, Technische Universität München, Marktoberdorf | website=daad.de | publisher=DAAD | location=Germany | date=2015 | accessdate=1 September 2015 }}</ref>
